      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, that's the core risk—you could be financially responsible for issues stemming from the relationship, even if the fault isn't entirely yours. Watch out for language that is overly broad, like \"any and all claims,\" or if you are indemnifying them for their own negligence. If the clause doesn't carve out exceptions for their own mistakes, it can be a very aggressive liability stance. It’s always best to negotiate carve-outs so you aren't liable for things outside your control.",
